"{\n  \"judgement\": \"The argument that popularity of a religion is not evidence of its validity is more defensible than the claim that it is, as the latter relies on a flawed assumption that a god would necessarily make itself known to everyone.\",\n  \"steering\": \"It's interesting to see how both sides are trying to make a point about the nature of evidence and proof. Maybe we can focus on the fact that many people find meaning and purpose in their faith, regardless of its popularity?\"\n}"